weewx-nut
Copyright 2025 Matthew Wall
Distributed under terms of the GPLv3

This is a driver for weewx that captures data from UPS/PDU devices using the
NUT client/server software.


===============================================================================
Installation

0) install pre-requisites

  a) install weewx
      http://weewx.com/docs
  b) install nut-client and possibly nut-server
      https://networkupstools.org/
  c) for local monitoring configure at least one device in nut
      sudo vi /etc/nut/ups.conf
      sudo systemctl restart nut-server

1) install the driver

weectl extension install https://github.com/matthewwall/weewx-nut/archive/master.zip

2) run the driver directly to verify functionality

export WEEWX_BINDIR=/usr/share/weewx
export WEEWX_USRDIR=/etc/weewx/bin/user
PYTHONPATH=$WEEWX_BINDIR python3 $WEEWX_USRDIR/nut.py

3) configure the driver

weectl station reconfigure --driver=user.nut

4) start weewx

sudo systemctl start weewx
